my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overall, safety shoes, hard hat with chin strap, gloves, etc.;
b) Make sure that the electric cord is in good condition; c) Never unplug the unit by pulling the cord; 
d) Do NOT use extension cords; e) Operate the unit with proper electric protection, especially if there is moisture of water; f) In the event of any electrical problem, STOP the unit using the switch identified with O-L, unplug the compressor from the incoming power and get assistance from the appropriate personnel.

a) The user must familiarise himself, before commencing using the compressor, with the content of the Manufacturer's Manual, WARNINGS, filling and operation procedures. 
b) Only use tanks that have been hydrostatically tested; 
c) Do NOT over pressurize the tanks. Pressurize only to working pressure, stamped on the shoulder of the tanks; d) Before starting filling the cylinders, make sure that all the safety devices are working properly as per Manufacturer's Manual; e) Check the tightness of the fittings using soapy water to check on possible leaks; f) Do NOT empty tanks completely , NOT even during when stocked for a longer period, this to avoid moisture in tanks; g) Do NOT climb on the machine;
h)Do NOT use the compressor to compress gases other that air, failure to do so can cause severe damage to the operator; 
i) DO NOT IMMERSE THE TANKS IN COLD WATER FOR ADDITIONAL COOLING DURING THE FILLING PROCESS. THIS MAY RESULT IN THE FORMING OF PERMANENT WATER DROPLETS IN THE TANK. THIS CONDENSATE CAN HARM THE USER OF THE AIR SEVERELY;  
j) The running period should not exceed 45 minutes in one filling. It should cool down for 15 minutes.
